Around [[1368 DR]],<ref> a [[gelatinous cube]] in the [[Maddgoth's Castle]] level of [[Undermountain]] had a ''cubic gate'' within it from one of the victims of a [[gorgon]].<ref>

Sometime in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]], a group of [[adventurer]]s traveling to the city of [[Ravens Bluff]] were attacked by a group of bandits led by the [[wizard]] [[Astrid]]. Among their ill-gotten loot the adventurers found a [[curse]]d ''cubic gate'' that instantly transported them to the [[Elemental Plane of Air]] and eventually the [[Negative Material Plane]].<ref>{{Cite organized play/LC/Plane Speaking|2,4,8}} There the planewalker [[Rowan Darkwood]] rescued the adventurers with a ''[[word of recall]]'' from death by [[negative energy]], taking them to the [[Astral Plane]]. Rowan quickly surmised that their ''cubic gate'' was cursed and that the adventurers would have to meet a certain requirement at each of its keyed planes if they wanted to get back home. He beseeched his patron [[deity]] [[Heimdall]] for guidance on the matter, but received only riddles as to how they had to progress.{{Cite organized play/LC/Plane Speaking|8-9}}

After treating the adventurers to a ''[[heroes' feast]]'', Rowan let them on their way. They proceeded to be taken by the ''cubic gate'' to the planes of [[Baator]], [[Bytopia]], [[Ysgard]],An exact name for the Prime Material world visited in ''Plane Speaking'' is never given, but everything shown about the world indicates it is most likely Athas, such as the prevalence of [[psionic]]s, sorcerer-kings in power, a scarcity of metal, a mention of [[w:c:darksun:preserver|preservers]], and the appearance of creatures from the Dark Sun setting.
